(17, 'madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar Adventure Trips - Explore Unique Landscapes', 'Excursiones en Madagascar: Aventura y Naturaleza', 'Discover unforgettable Madagascar adventure trips!', 'Descubre emocionantes excursiones en Madagascar.', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'img/uploads/images/img_6863d71401f328.28687522.webp', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(43, 43, 43); font-family: InterRegular; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">While Madagascar is an island in the Indian Ocean, it was originally settled by people of Indonesian and African descent, which you can clearly see when one looks at the inhabitants. Others have suggested that the people of Madagascar descended from Indonesians and Africans who mixed before their arrival on the isolated island, but studies prove people of Madagascar came from Borneo and Africa. It is not fully known how the inhabitants came there or if they were there already. Only later did Arabs, Indians and Jewish immigrants mix into the population of the island. The Malagasy way of thinking is a mixture of cultures, as well as their appearance and fashion style.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(43, 43, 43); font-family: InterRegular; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">While Madagascar is an island in the Indian Ocean, it was originally settled by people of Indonesian and African descent, which you can clearly see when one looks at the inhabitants. Others have suggested that the people of Madagascar descended from Indonesians and Africans who mixed before their arrival on the isolated island, but studies prove people of Madagascar came from Borneo and Africa. It is not fully known how the inhabitants came there or if they were there already. Only later did Arabs, Indians and Jewish immigrants mix into the population of the island. The Malagasy way of thinking is a mixture of cultures, as well as their appearance and fashion style.</span></p>', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(18, 'information', 'Information', 'Información', 'Madagascar Eco Tours: Explore Nature Responsibly', 'Excursiones sostenibles en Madagascar - Madagascar Green Tours', 'Discover unforgettable Madagascar eco tours today!', 'Descubre excursiones sostenibles en Madagascar.', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'img/uploads/images/img_6863d6ef291279.67165247.webp', 'Information', 'Información', 'Information', 'Información', 'Information', 'Información', '<p>info</p>', '<p>info</p>', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(19, 'contact', 'Contact', 'Contáctenos', 'Madagascar Travel Inquiries - Contact Us Today', 'Contacto Madagascar Green Tours - ¡Conéctate con nosotros!', 'Get answers to your Madagascar travel inquiries here.', 'Contacto Madagascar Green Tours para tus consultas.', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'img/uploads/images/img_6863d6b453ed82.53910758.webp', 'Contact', 'Contáctenos', 'Contact', 'Contáctenos', 'Contact', 'Contáctenos', '<p><br></p>', '<p><br></p>', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(20, 'gallery', 'Gallery', 'Galería', 'Madagascar Nature Photography Gallery', 'Galería de Tours en Madagascar - Madagascar Green Tours', 'Explore Stunning Madagascar Nature Photography', 'Descubre nuestra galería de tours en Madagascar.', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'img/uploads/images/img_6863d8c53e4162.15630622.webp', 'Discover Madagascar through our photo gallery. Every image tells a story.', 'Descubra Madagascar a través de nuestra galería de fotos. Cada imagen cuenta una historia.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(21, 'madagascar-tour-guide', 'Madagascar Tour Guide', 'Madagascar Tour Guide', 'Local and experienced guide in Madagascar – Your travel partner', 'Guía de viajes en Madagascar: Explora lo mejor de la isla', 'Descubre la guía de viajes en Madagascar y planifica tu aventura.', 'Explore Madagascar with an experienced local tourist guide. Safety, authenticity, and cultural immersion guaranteed for an unforgettable journey.', 'Madagascar Tour Guide', 'Madagascar Tour Guide', 'img/uploads/images/img_6863d8c53e4162.15630622.webp', 'Local and experienced guide in Madagascar – Your travel partner', 'Local and experienced guide in Madagascar – Your travel partner', 'Your experienced guide in Madagascar for a unique journey', '', '', '', '<p>Are you looking for a <strong>local guide in Madagascar</strong> to discover\r\nthe cultural and natural richness of the Great Island?<br>\r\nOur team of experienced and passionate guides, fluent in French, English, and\r\nSpanish, is ready to accompany you at every stage of your trip.<o:p></o:p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>With their deep knowledge of the country and professionalism, our <strong>tourist\r\nguides in Madagascar</strong> ensure a safe, authentic, and enriching travel\r\nexperience.<o:p></o:p></p>', '<p>Are you looking for a <strong>local guide in Madagascar</strong> to discover\r\nthe cultural and natural richness of the Great Island?<br>\r\nOur team of experienced and passionate guides, fluent in French, English, and\r\nSpanish, is ready to accompany you at every stage of your trip.<o:p></o:p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>With their deep knowledge of the country and professionalism, our <strong>tourist\r\nguides in Madagascar</strong> ensure a safe, authentic, and enriching travel\r\nexperience.<o:p></o:p></p>', '2025-09-15 13:02:54', '2025-09-15 13:02:54');
INSERT INTO `reviews` (`id`, `rating`, `name_user`, `email_user`, `message`, `pending`, `daty`) VALUES
(1, 0, 'Ingrid', '', 'We visited Madagascar in October 2009. Our plan was to travel from Tulear to Tana by taxi brousse. In Tulear we met Baba and he could drive us to Tana for a very reasonable price. We made a good choice, he is a good driver, very helpful and he gave us a lot of information about Madagascar. On the way to Tana we visited Isalo, Ambalavao, Ranomafana, Ambositra and Antsirabe. Because we saved a lot of time by travelling with a private car, we had time left to visit Andasibe and Mahavelona. Baba gave us good advice about the hotels. We had a great time and we recommend Baba to anyone who thinks about visiting Madagascar.', 0, '2012-08-07 07:40:14'),
(2, 0, 'Muriam', 'muriam@gmail.om', 'To all visitors of this site: I can really recommend Baba. He is a great driver, knows what travellers wants to see and where to stop. The hotels he recommends are always on a good location, great settings en clean/comfortable rooms. In short: he knows exactly what is important for us travellers.\r\n\r\nWe hired him as a driver on our holiday last year for actually 12 days, because of the good experience we prolonged it with 4 days more. Also thanks to Baba I have very good memories about the holiday in Madagascar.', 0, '2013-09-07 07:40:53'),
(3, 0, 'Alleras', 'alleras@gmail.com', 'We\'ve been travelling around the world and this last trip to Madagascar has been one of the best experience we\'ve had! Travelling by yourself in Madagascar is not easy at all, you need someone to guide you and give you some advice, our experience with Baba has been really great! He\'s been kind and friendly with us, he made us feel as a close friend, giving good recommendations and making us understand and know the culture and local traditions......\r\n\r\nNo comments about the car, one of the best you can find in Madagascar!!!\r\nDon\'t hesitate in arranging a trip with him, for sure you won\'t regret! If you have any doubt or question please feel free to send me and e-mail asking for further information!\r\nGood luck and enjoy Mada!\"', 0, '2014-11-15 07:41:26'),
(4, 0, 'Erik Muller', 'erikonderweg@gmail.com', 'We are currently on trip with Baba and it is fabulous! He\'s a great and pleasant guide and really knows what he is talking about.\r\n', 0, '2015-06-07 07:42:00'),
(5, 0, 'Marion Vanwieringen', 'Marionvanwieringen@mac.com', 'We have had a wonderful trip with Baba in Madagascar. We started with the river trips on the Tsiribihina river. It was so great with Charlie as our cook, three boatmen and Baba as our guide. We camped on sanbanks near the river. We saw a lot of wildlife like crocodiles, lemu, cameleon, tortue and lots of birds. After that we went to the Tsingy. Great adventure with a 4x4 and a very good driver; Patrick. We stayed in a nice bungalow and Charlie made dinner and lunch. A visit to the Tsingy is well worth. It is amazing these stones and also the wildlife. From the Tsingy we drove to Morondava and stopped for the sunset in Baobab Allée. So beautiful! From Morondava back to Antsirabe and then to the south; one day in Ambositra, then to Ranomafana, Andringitra (climbed peak Boby with Adrien, incredible experience!) and finally to Isalo. Baba was very helpful and gave us lots of advices during our trips. He is very punctual and you can discuss everything with him, really perfect. From the south we went back to the north and stayed one night in Fianar. We ended our holiday in Andasibe. Baba arranged again the best guide in the park; Florent. We saw the Indri Indri, bamboo lemur, Sifaka (lots), chameleons, frogs, birds, etc. Back in Tana we asked Baba to find us a 2CV to bring us to the airport and he arranged one. We thank Baba for everything, we had a perfect holiday. We were especially happy that Baba dit not put us in mixed groups, but we were always the two of us with a local guide. We will recommend everyone who wants to visit Madagascar to book with Madagascar Green Tours. If you have any questions, don\'t hesitate to send us an e-mail', 0, '2016-07-07 08:05:38'),
(6, 0, 'koschka', 'koschka@libero.it', 'I have just come back from my 10-day trip to Madagascar as a solo female traveller with Baba: what a great experience! Baba is a very friendly and knowledgeable guide, with a strong sense for customer satisfaction. Very professional and attentive to his clients\' needs, he tailors the tour accordingly and is always open to suggestions. I felt happy and safe at all times. Please feel free to email me if you have any questions: I will be happy to share my experience with you. Great job Baba', 0, '2016-06-09 11:13:24'),
(7, 0, 'David , Núria , Quim i Carme', 'davit@miarto.dr', '-Una amiga nos recomendó viajar a Madagascar y hacerlo con un guía local experto y altamente recomendable: Baba y su agencia: Magascascar Green Tours. -Hemos sido dos parejas :David, Núria, Quim i Carme. Somos de Calonge y Sant Feliu de Guíxols en Girona. -Estuvimos en contacto previamente por e-mail para planear nuestro viaje, ver sus sugerencias y decidir el alojamiento. -Octu-e dia 2 llegada a Tana-dia 23 salida de Tana a París. -Hemos empezado haciendo el descenso del Rio Tsiribina( altamente recomendable) Escogió a un equipo fantàstico de remeros ( Karla, Terry y Dadi) y el cocinero Dady . Todo el equipo nos sorprendió con su simpatia, recibimiento, experiencia..nos sorprendieron con sus platos, el \"punch\", los postres...y conocimiento del territorio. -Posteriormente magnífico conductor de 4x4 en Belo sur Tsiribina para viajar a visitar los Grand Tsingy. Impresionante el lugar, Richard gran profesional con su Toyota , visitamos la Avenida de los Baobabs y Morondava. -Allí final de la primera etapa, dura ( calor, recorridos...) pero altamente recomendable... -Ahora nos esperaba la segunda etapa: Morondava-Tulear. Baba ya nos esperaba en el Aeropuerto y nos trasladó al Puerto de Tulear para viajar al paraíso, a decansar: ANAKAO ( lo mejor de Madagascar , sin duda!) Muy recomendable estar 3 dias para decansar y visitar la isla de Nosy ve...impresionante el lugar, la gente, la tranquilidad, la riqueza de los fondos marinos, impresionante barrera de arrecifes coralinos llenos de vida. Si podeis por presupuesto ir a Anakao Ocean Lodge....maravilloso, lo mejor de Madagascar! -A la vuelta Baba ya nos esperaba con su magnífico coche un turismo familiar Hyundai de 7 plazas ( para 5 personas) , el coche muy confortable. -Visitamos Isalo NP ( Piscina natural), Ambalavao ( PApel, Seda, arrozales, Anjà ( Lemures de Cola anillada...) -Siempre ha escogido buenos establecimientos y hemos estado confortablemente alojados. -LLegada a Fianar, viaje en tren a Manakara ( No os lo perdais...experiencia única !) -En Manakara, Baba nos esperaba, siempre -Magnífica excursión por el Canal de Pangalanes , y siempre escogiendo buenos guías. -Trayecto hacia Ranomafana NP , donde estuvimos bien alojados, buena comida y otro guía muy profesional con gran experiencia en ornitologia ( escogido por Baba). -Posteriormente Ambositra, Antsirabe ( Visitas a familia que hace artesania con el cuerno del zebú, visita a la zona termal y instalaciones termales, visita a miniaturas de pousse-pousse...muy recomendable !) -Posteriormente Antananarivo y vuelo a Sainte Marie, alojados en Hotel en la Ille aux Nattes ( preciosa, paradisíaca, muy buena gente en la isla, diferentes hoteles magníficos...) -Tres dias de desconexión y vuelta a Tana -Visita a Anadasibe ( Indri-Indri, etc, excusion nocturna: lemures ratón, camaleones...buenos guias) -Muy buena estancia en Madagascar, muy buenos consejos, siempre buenas recomendaciones, Baba y su equipo: magnífica gente. Nos hemos sentido muy bien acogidos, seguros, y acompañados de un gran profesional. No dudeis, muy buena opción y muy buen precio !! -Gracias Baba !! Volveremos a Madagascar !!', 0, '2017-08-07 08:06:29'),
(8, 0, 'Margreta', '123margreta@gmail.com', 'I did the birdtour. If you want some information please mail me', 0, '2018-09-07 11:11:36'),
(9, 0, 'Hans and Inja from NL', 'hans_van_wijk@hotmail.com', 'We are just back from our lovely 3 weeks holiday in Madagascar. Thanks to Baba! First we found it a bit difficult to meet with someone you don`t know and having cash money with you.... However, Baba quickly gained our confidence! We did 2 Tours with Baba. One 11 day tour driving down the RN7 with the Manakara train tour and a 2 day tour to the Indri indri`s. Baba is a good guide and listens good to his customers needs and is a safe driver. He seems to know everybody during the way :wink: (Talking to everybody and making jokes) He also knows the good local guides in the Parcs, due to his experience. He is a helpfull guide aswell! Especially since our bagage arrived 12 days later then we did. He helped us to arrange our cloths and bathing materials etc. We can truly recommend Baba for being your guide. If you have any questions, feel free to sent us an email.', 0, '2018-09-12 11:13:03'),
(10, 0, 'Ana Gomez (Spain)', 'amgortiz@hotmail.com', 'My partner and I visited Madagascar in 2008, and we were so lucky to have Baba as our guide. He\'s not only professional, but he\'s so very kind...We really enjoyed the journey traveling with Baba. It was a great experience and we highly recommend it!!', 0, '2019-08-07 08:07:52'),
(11, 0, 'xavier hasen', '', 'From the pickup at Antananarivo airport to the drop off after 9 amazing days of discovering Madagascar’s unique nature and culture, we felt very well taken care of and safe with our driver/guide Desi and the team at Madagascar green tours.\r\nDesi is very experienced super knowledgeable about everything your want to know about Madagascar and its history. The car was extremely well maintained and clean and Desi’s driving made us feel safe despite the many potholes and narrow “highways”.\r\nBaba, the company’s owner, met us twice during the trip and made sure\r\neverything was going well. We felt particularly well looked after, as this trip was part of our honeymoon!\r\nWe would highly recommend this company to anyone wishing to travel in Madagascar.', 0, '2019-11-07 08:08:41'),
(12, 0, 'PATRICK CERPENTIER', 'patrickcerpentier@hotmail.com', 'During the month of september 2019 we travelled through the amazing country Madagascar for more than 3 weeks and we can highly recommend Madagascar Green Tours from Baba Solomon.\r\nMadagascar Green Tours is a very reliable company and mister Baba is a very kind and honest person and fulfilled all our special requests. He was providing us also a very good car (4 WD Toyota Landcruiser HJ 100) - needful for this country - and an experienced and safe driver, mr. Tsoa.\r\nWhen we are going a second time to this beautiful country (because there is a lot to see), we definitively will again choose his company - without any doubt.\r\nWe are so grateful for providing us an unforgettable and fantastic beautiful trip.\r\nThank you so much mister Baba and Tsoa.\r\nMadagascar was really a dream destination !', 0, '2019-10-07 08:09:03'),
(13, 0, 'Joan Anton', 'joananton.bofarull@gmail.com', '25 días con Madagascar Green Tours\r\nHemos vivido 25 intensos días en nuestro viaje por Madagascar siempre acompañados por el guía Tsiory y, la mayor parte del tiempo, también por el conductor Alain. Los dos han trabajado para que todo fuera bien. Tsiory, especialmente, ha sido un acompañante perfecto y atento que nos ha hecho sentir siempre a gusto en nuestro recorrido por la isla. Tsiory y Baba, en contacto permanente, han resuelto todos los imprevistos que han surgido: pequeños cambios, retraso vuelo interno, necesidad de moneda local... Hemos dormido en tiendas de campaña y en hoteles maravillosos. Hemos estado en muchos parques naturales, en ciudades y aldeas y en playas idílicas. También hemos sufrido las “carreteras” de Madagascar :). En resumen, una muy buena relación calidad - precio y una agencia fiable. Con palabras de Baba: ¡yo confío, tu confías!', 0, '2019-12-07 08:09:31'),
(14, 0, 'Horacio Gil ', 'horacioriocionus@hotmail.com', 'I am from Spain and I have been visiting Madagascar from 13 to 29 October 2022 with Madagascar Green Tours. We have enjoyed so much this incredible country. The National Parks are full of plants and animals that you can\'t find in any part of the world, except in Madagascar. I have millions of pictures of lemurs, baobabs and chameleons. Malagasy people are amazing with a smile always in their faces. I have enjoyed also the typical Malagasy dishes and i have earned a few kilos after this superb trip. The only thing I can complain is the long car trips for the horrible roads, but the effort was worthy. I can say that the service of this company and especially from his owner Baba was excellent, taking care of us all the time and including a list of amazing hotels where we were accommodated. I strongly recommend coming Madagascar and the services of Madagascar Green Tours. If you are interested in more details, you can contact me by email: horacioricinus@hotmail.com.', 0, '2022-10-31 16:42:22'),
(15, 0, 'Bea', 'beatrizbb26@hotmail.com', 'No puedo más que agradecer a Baba y a Madagascar Green Tours el recorrido que hicimos por el país. La organización impecable, perfecta, todo el personal que trabaja o colabora con ellos son de diez. Si estás pensando en conocer Madagascar puedes confiar en ellos, son super profesionales y se preocupan a diario en que disfrutes de Madagascar en todo momento del viaje. Gracias Baba porque nuestro viaje fue espectacular y tenemos un recuerdo imborrable del viaje', 0, '2022-11-18 12:52:29'),
(16, 0, 'Rune Åsland', 'runeasland@gmail.com', 'We have been visiting Madegascar from 6th to 25th April 2023.Arrived Antananarivo and spent one night here before we went to Nosy Be for 10 days at Andilana Beach hotel.This is not a must , but recommended.Back to Antananarivo where we were picked up by Baba and drove east to Andasibe National Park. The 5 hours slow walk in the park was very plesant and enjoyable.After our stay in the east we drove west to visit Morondava to watch the spectacular Baobab trees.Before continuing for Morondava we visited Antisirabe and the former Norwegian Missionary station.Since the route back to Antananarivo is the same as the already experienced with the 2 days challenging roads, you may consider to take a flight back to Antananarivo.However all credits to Mr. Baba who is an excellent driver and made our trip unforgettable.Returning to Norway, our thoughts are how kindly and happy the people of Madagascar are, despite their challenge with poorness and lack of western technology.We highly recommend a roundtrip in beautifuly Madagascar with Baba Green Tours.Br. Rune & Nina', 0, '2023-04-30 12:10:57'),
(17, 0, 'Carme and Joan', 'csilvest@xtec.cat', 'We would like to express our gratitude and share our posivitve feedback for Madagascar Green Tours . The company completely responded to our needs and our 21-day trip was outstanding. Booking and communications were great prior to departure.\r\nWe were incredibly well looked after by Baba,our tour guides, local guides and drivers who were very professional, knowlegable,informative and helpful and sorted out any changes for us. Evertything we asked for was granted; the airport pick ups and drops were perfectly on time. Our tour guides and drivers were always punctual. Accommodation was great.\r\nThank you Baba and team for making the trip memorable for us!! Relying on a local company like this one is a must for everyone who wants to visit Madagascar and make their visit one of a lifetime. Definitely will recommend it!!\r\nCarme and Joan', 0, '2023-10-13 08:54:30'),
(18, 0, 'elliot.damashek@gmail.com', 'elliot.damashek@gmail.com', 'We had an amazing experience with Madagascar Green Tours, and would recommend the company without hesitation to any travelers to Madagascar. We had a clear itinerary and everything was well-organized, from comfortable hotels to guided tours in Madagascar\'s national parks. We loved the unique experiences we had in Madagascar - the animals and the landscapes in particular.\r\n\r\nWe spent a 13 day trip with our guide Andrey and driver Alain, coordinated by Baba. All 3 were exceedingly professional throughout. As our guide, Andrey explained so many interesting things to us and went out of his way to make us comfortable, like giving up his seat for my carsick wife and guiding us to a pharmacy and groceries when we needed them. As our driver, Alain was an absolute workhorse on the bumpy Malagasy roads. We noticed all the little things he did, like opening the door for us every time or cleaning the van before every day on the road.\r\n\r\nOverall, our time with Madagascar Green Tours was incredible and we have no doubt that you\'ll have a great time with them.', 0, '2023-10-13 08:56:40'),
(19, 0, 'Christina', 'cbrunner@bluewin.ch', 'I had a unforgettable, well organized and safe trip with Madagascar Green Tours. I recommend them very high. For more then four weeks I was traveling with Alain (Driver) and Samson (Guide). Both are very competent in their job and where always there for me. With professional knowledge, always friendly and courteous they made my trip amazing and unique. Every Morning the car was cleaned and Alain opened the door for me. He is a incredible driver. Always on time, careful and safe driving on all conditions of the Roads. Samson gave me a lot of information about Madagascar history, nature and culture. He organized for me individual tours and guides in the Nationalparcs, because I like to do bird watching and taking bird photos. Thank you very much Alain and Samson: I had a great time with you.\r\nBecause of my long stay, I made a self costumised journey . Baba organized my trip together with me and considered my ideas and wishes in every way it was possible. On tour he informed me very promptly about every change. As I was not happy in a Hotel (the environment at the room was very noisy), he organized very fast a beautiful Hotel in a quiet and lovely surrounding. Thank you very much Alain, Samson and Baba. ', 0, '2023-10-28 09:54:00'),
(150, 0, 'Lucy', 'meyer.lucy@outlook.com', 'We had such an amazing time with Baba on our RN7 tour through Madagascar. I contacted Baba in February for a 7 day tour in April/May for 7 people and we are so happy that we chose to book Madagascar Green Tours :). Communication with him was great and he was very open to our requests (like only booking Malagasy-owned hotels). Upon arrival, we immediately felt very safe and comfortable with him as our guide and driver. Baba is a wonderful human being who loves sharing his knowledge of the Malagasy culture, with whom you can always joke around and also sit comfortably in silence. Our highlights included visiting the rain forest in Ranomafana, spotting Lemurs in Anja Community Reserve and hiking in Isalo National Park etc. Each time Baba organised fantastic local tour guides who really knew their way around the area and the animals. It felt like Baba knew a lot of people everywhere we went and everyone was always happy to see him. He always went above and beyond to make sure we had a great time - so much so that sometimes we felt like we needed to make sure he looked after his needs as well. He even went more than the extra mile when 2 of our group needed help organising transportation from Tulear to Antananarivo after our time with him (we spent about a week without him in Anakao, Tulear and Antananarivo). Baba, thank you so much for everything, we will never forget our road trip and hope to be back soon to see different parts of Madagascar! Misaotra Betsaka Baba! All the best, your Chicken Crew :)', 0, '2024-05-21 09:24:05'),
(151, 0, 'Marie Ueland Quignard', 'marie_uq@hotmail.com', 'Loved our trip with Baba and Madagascar green tours. From the very start Baba organized a customized trip for me and three friends. We had soo many desires and questions before coming to Madagascar which Baba met and answerd with no hesitation. We started in Antananrivo, drove to Antsirabe to Morondova, back and to Andasibe with a total of 10 days with Baba as our guide and driver. The hours in the car was long, but Baba made sure we were comfortable, and shared so much knowledge and humor along the way. And even though the time spent on the road could be long, there was so much to see, a lot of pitstops and changing scenery which made the drive eventfull, interesting and picturesque. As well as showing us around his very beautiful country and introducing us to locals, he made sure to let us know about the culture, way of life and teaching us a bit of the language. He also made it possible for us to visit a hospital to donate medical equipment (MUCH needed and recommended if you find yourself with \"left over\" medical supply before you leave for Madagascar) which made a lasting impression, as well as setting us up with people to whom we could donate warm clothes/shoes ect. \r\nAfter Andasibe we headed up North to Diego Suarez on another 6 days trip, where we met up with Vohangi. Our trip in the North took us from Diego, Montagne d\'Ambre, Red Tsingy and Ankarana and yet again Vohangi showed exceptional knowledge about her country, people, nature and animals (everything we find super interesting). And driver Jean Claude drove us safely throughout our journy in the North. \r\nThe center and North of Madagascar is very different and I would really recommend doing them both. Unfortunately time did not allow us to also do the south, so that will have to be for next time. \r\nWe\'re overextatic with our trip and everything that Baba and his team has done for us, and would highly recommend Madagascar Green Tours to anyone going to Madagascar.', 0, '2024-07-23 04:03:42'),
(152, 0, 'Lulu', 'luana.barra@me.com', 'We, a group of seven friends from Switzerland, decided to travel to Madagascar together in April. From the start, we knew we had a limited budget and only two weeks to explore this vast country. Initially, we thought we\'d plan everything on our own – but fortunately, we discovered Baba Salomon and Madagascar Green Tours. This turned out to be one of the best decisions we could have made.\r\n\r\nRight from the beginning of our planning, Baba was incredibly accommodating. He took all our wishes into account, always prioritizing our satisfaction and our desire to support the local community. Planning with him was so effortless that we boarded our flight with peace of mind, knowing we were in good hands. Hours later, we were warmly welcomed by Baba Salomon at the airport.\r\n\r\nOur journey then began: Baba Salomon drove us from Antananarivo northwards to Tulear. The journey with him lasted eight days until he had to bid us farewell in Tulear. We had the best time with Baba, not only because he made us feel safe every moment but also because he shared so much about Madagascar that no one else could. Baba knows the country inside out, and amusingly, many people seem to know Baba. This didn’t surprise us, as he is a genuinely kind-hearted person, exceptionally friendly, always with a smile on his face, making us feel truly comfortable.\r\n\r\nThe itinerary Baba put together for us was also fantastic. Despite our short time, we saw so much of Madagascar. Our highlights included Ranomafana National Park, Isalo National Park, and the Anja Park Reserve. Even the long drives through the country were a highlight in themselves.\r\n\r\nBaba Salomon and his agency, Madagascar Green Tours, come highly recommended! Our trip with him was unforgettable. Misaotra Betsaka Baba! Your chicken crew', 0, '2024-07-30 14:16:23'),
(156, 5, 'Benoit Maheux', 'bmaheux@hotmail.com', 'Amazing local team and we were so grateful to get Tahina as driver. He was just amazing with my whole family and we will remember our 3 weeks itinerary for a long time. Out of 15 destinations over a 9 month span, Madagascar was my favorite destination. <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rEmaEklG0Ek\" target=\"_blank\">www.youtube.com/loicmaheux</a>', 0, '2024-09-11 19:37:12'),
(157, 5, 'Markus', 'bbaker@gmx.de', 'There are not enough stars for this top notch company!!! :)\n\nWe spent 25 days in Madagascar and from the planning of our journey to the guides, the drivers, the accommodations, just everything provided by Madagascar Green Tours was awesome!\n\nOur fluently english speaking guide Samson had a lot of interesting stories about the people, the country\'s different tribes and diverse landscapes. Besides that it was just nice to chat and/or to have a laugh with him;)\n\nThe drivers Njaka and Papoose did a great job taking us from one destination to the other...due to the often very poor road conditions this was not an easy task! Our 4WD cars were in perfect condition so the sometimes very long drives were easy to handle for us.\nRegarding the hotels/lodges: We can\'t think of any better options in Madagascar. For us it seemed that Madagascar Green Tours always chose the best accommodation wherever we stayed.\n\nThe whole trip was mindblowing and after spending 25 days with Samson, Njaka and Papoose we can honestly say that Madagascar will always have a special place in our hearts...thanks to Baba and Madagascar Green Tours!!!', 0, '2024-09-24 15:46:54'),
